casebody.data:
S. Charles Welsh, v. The Metropolitan Elevated Railroad Company, (action No. 2.) Decided January 6, 1890.

Before Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

Per Curiam.

The questions presented on this appeal are all determined by the decision in Welsh v. The Metropolitan El. Ry. Co., action No. 1. See ante, page 408. For the reasons there stated the judgment should be affirmed with costs.
